<TITLE> BSF kills cowherd in Satkhira </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, Apr 2 (bdnews24.com)  A Bangladeshi cowherd was shot dead by Indian border forces at Baikari in Shatkhira early Friday. The dead was identified as Saiful Islam, 28, son of Abdus Sattar of Ghona village of the upazila. Abdul Bari, sub-inspector of Satkhira Sadar Police Station, said a group consists of 6/7 cowherds had crossed the border on the night of March 31. The Indian Border Security Force (BSF) shot at them as they were returning home with cows on Friday. Saiful died on the spot. The BSF dumped the body in Bangladesh territory at Baladghata near pillar 7. Major Jahangir Hossain, operation officer of BDR 41 Rifles Battalions confirmed the incident. He said Saiful's body bore two bullet wound
